goals.question: What is the distribution of miles driven?

goals.visualization: scatter plot of miles vs gas
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the relationship between miles driven and gas used, and if there is any correlation between the two variables.

goals.question: What is the distribution of years of car manufacture?

goals.question: What is the average amount of gas used per year?
goals.visualization: line chart of gas by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend of gas usage over the years and if there is any significant change in the average amount of gas used per year.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='green', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['gas'] = pd.to_numeric(data['gas'], errors='coerce')
    data['miles'] = pd.to_numeric(data['miles'], errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    plt.xlabel('Miles Driven')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Used (Gallons)')
    plt.title('How does the amount of gas used vary with miles driven?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    plt.hist(data['year'], bins=55, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['year'].min(), color='red', label='Min year: {:.2f}'.format(data['year'].min().year))
    plt.axvline(data['year'].max(), color='green', label='Max year: {:.2f}'.format(data['year'].max().year))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of years of car manufacture?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['side'] = data['side'].astype('category')
    chart = data.boxplot(column='miles', by='side', figsize=(8,6))
    chart.set_xlabel('Side of the steering wheel')
    chart.set_ylabel('Miles driven')
    chart.set_title('How does the position of the steering wheel affect miles driven?')
    chart.axhline(y=data['miles'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median miles driven: {:.2f}'.format(data['miles'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('year')['gas'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['gas'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Gas usage', 'Average gas usage'])
    plt.title('What is the average amount of gas used per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
